%% ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
%% C. UK Access / Evidence Status — traffic light table
%% ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
%% GREEN — NICE-recommended / commissioned:
%%   - Ibrutinib (TA502) for R/R MCL after one previous line
%%   - Zanubrutinib (TA1081) for R/R MCL after one previous line
%%   - Brexucabtagene autoleucel (TA677) for post-BTKi R/R MCL, CDF
%%
%% AMBER — evidence-supported but access-dependent:
%%   - TRIANGLE ibrutinib-integrated first-line (fit patients)
%%   - Acalabrutinib + BR (ECHO) — NICE GID-TA11091 in development
%%   - Ibrutinib + venetoclax (SYMPATICO) — non-routine NICE funding
%%
%% RED — not routine NHS-funded / investigational:
%%   - Pirtobrutinib — UK access should not be assumed
%%   - Lisocabtagene maraleucel in MCL — UK access uncertain
%%   - SHINE pattern (frontline ibrutinib + BR) — not adopted as UK routine
%%
%% GREY — emerging / conference-level:
%%   - MRD-guided treatment changes outside trials
%%   - Bispecific T-cell engagers in MCL (glofitamab, epcoritamab)
%%   - ASH/EHA 2024–2025 emerging abstracts
%%
%% Reminder line:
%% "Evidence-supported does not equal NHS-commissioned."
